In [[Scotland]], the [[English]] are sometimes referred to as the '''Auld Enemy''' (Old enemy), especially now in a sporting context.
 
The worst Scots nightmare, a 'gubbing' by the Auld Enemy, England beating Scotland.

This phrase refers to the long history of conflict between the two countries.

